    <!-- Post Career -->
    <section id="after" class="bg-light">
        <div class="container">
            <div style="border-bottom: solid; margin-bottom: 40px;">
                <h2>Post Career Benefits: <span style="font-style: italic;">Income For Your Future</span></h2>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-12 mx-auto">
                    <div class="panels animated fadeInUp" id="accordion2">
                        <h3 class="accordionheader">
                          <i class="fa fa-plus"></i>401(k) Savings Plan
                        </h3>
                        <div class="posts">
                            <article>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">Benefits:</h4>
                                <p>A savings plan for retirement</p>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">How It Works:</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>You will be automatically enrolled in the pre-tax 401(k) contribution each year equal to the maximum permitted by law, unless you choose otherwise. The maximum contribution for 2018 is $18,500.</li>
                                    <li>Your team matches 140% of your pre-tax savings, to a maximum of $25,900.</li>
                                    <li>You can also contribute an additional amount on an after-tax basis.</li>
                                    <li>All contributions are credited with investment earnings/losses while in the plan. You select investments from a menu of options.</li>
                                    <li>All contribution and investments earnings grow tax-deferred while in the plan.</li>
                                    <li>All contributions are always 100% vested.</li>
                                </ul>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">Who to Contact:</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><span class="font-weight-bold"><a href="https://voyaretirement.voya.com" target="_blank">Voya Website</a> </span> or call: <a href="tel:800-584-6001">800-584-6001</a></li>
                                </ul>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">Important Documents:</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/c4w5kpjhhbhssll/NBA%20Players%27%20401%28k%29.pdf?dl=0" target="_blank">Summary Plan Description</a></li>
                                </ul>
                            </article>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="accordionheader">
                          <i class="fa fa-plus"></i>NBA Players’ Pension Plan
                        </h3>
                        <div class="posts">
                            <article>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">Benefits:</h4>
                                <p>A plan that provides income for retirement</p>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">How It Works:</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Your pension benefit grows with each year you play in the league (subject to IRS maximum benefit limits).</li>
                                    <li>Once you play three seasons, you can receive your normal retirement monthly benefit at age 50 or reduced benefit as early as age 45; a portion of your benefit may be available as a lump sum.</li>
                                </ul>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">Who to Contact:</h4>
                                <p>Zenith American Solutions (ZAS) is the Pension Plan's third-party administrator and provides pension benefit administrative services. They are your point of contact for all pension inquiries.</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><a href="tel:833-622-7529">833 NBA-PLAY (622-7529)</a></li>
                                    <li><a href="mailto:NBAPlayerPension@zenith-american.com">Email</a> </li>
                                    <li><a href="https://auth.mygameplan.com/Auth/ClientLogon_NBA.aspx?Client=NBA&Target=https%3a%2f%2fwww.mygameplan.com%2fAuthMgr.aspx%3fReturnUrl%3d%252fdefault.aspx" target="_blank">mygameplan.com</a> (for personalized information)</li>
                                </ul>
                            </article>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="accordionheader">
                          <i class="fa fa-plus"></i>Health Reimbursement Account Plan
                        </h3>
                        <div class="posts">
                            <article>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">Benefit:</h4>
                                <p>A health care reimbursement account you can use to pay for health care expenses or to obtain coverage post-career</p>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">How It Works:</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>A reimbursement account you can use for out-of-pocket health care costs (e.g., copayments, deductibles, prescription medication, hospital or optical dispensing service costs) while you are playing or for certain health care coverage or costs post-career.</li>
                                    <li>Each year you play, you receive contributions to your account; also grows through investment returns. If you are eligible, your HRA contribution each season will be the lesser of $30,000 or the difference between $150,000 and the sum of all contributions previously made to your HRA provided the difference is greater than $0. Once you play three seasons, you will be able to access your account funds.</li>
                                    <li>Contributions are not taxed and benefits are tax-free.</li>
                                    <li>File a claim for reimbursement, or use your plan debit card to pay expenses for yourself and any eligible dependents (including children up through the end of the year in which they reach age 26).</li>
                                </ul>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">Who to Contact:</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><a href="https://www.umr.com/tpa-ap-web/?page=defaultRoot" target="_blank">UMR (formerly POMCO) Website</a> or call <a href="tel:866-542-7958">866-542-7958</a></li>
                                </ul>
                            </article>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="accordionheader">
                          <i class="fa fa-plus"></i>NBA Players’ Post Career Income Plan
                        </h3>
                        <div class="posts">
                            <article>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">Benefits:</h4>
                                <p>A plan that provides guaranteed monthly income soon after your NBA career ends and continuing until your pension begins</p>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">How It Works:</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Plan provides guaranteed monthly income through insured annuities soon after your NBA career ends (but not before age 30).</li>
                                    <li>You receive a collectively bargained team contribution each year you play (a portion of which is tax-deferred); in addition, you may elect to contribute 2%, 5%, 7% or 10% of your eligible pay.</li>
                                    <li>You may choose from various annuity payment options, including monthly payments until age 50 or lifetime payments.</li>
                                </ul>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">Who to Contact:</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><a href="https://principal.com/NBAPlayers">Principal Financial Group Website</a> or call: <a href="tel:866-541-6351">866-541-6351</a></li>
                                </ul>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">Important Documents:</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/zzapu5od53gimhb/NBA%20Plan%20Overview-1.pdf?dl=0" target="_blank">Plan Overview</a></li>
                                </ul>
                                
                            </article>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="accordionheader">
                          <i class="fa fa-plus"></i>NBA Players’ Retiree Medical Plan
                        </h3>
                        <div class="posts">
                            <article>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">Benefits:</h4>
                                <p>Healthcare coverage for eligible retired players and their families</p>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">How It Works:</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        The plan provides healthcare coverage through UnitedHealthcare® for eligible retired players and, in some cases, their families at no charge to the player for the cost of premiums for such coverage.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        You can use any provider for medical care, although using a UnitedHealthcare® network provider generally reduces your out-of- pocket costs.
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                <h4 class="font-weight-bold">Who to Contact:</h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><span class="font-weight-bold">NBA Players’ Health Service Center:</span> <a href="tel:855-497-6669">855-497-6669</a>, Option 2
                                    </li>
                                    <li><span class="font-weight-bold"><a href="https://www.myuhc.com" target="_blank">United Healthcare Website</a></span></li>
                                </ul>
                            </article>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p>This summary is intended to provide highlights of your benefits. If there is any conflict between this summary and the applicable legal plan document, as amended, the legal plan document, as amended, shall govern at all times.</p>
        </div>
